@ct<ENG>Adon Olam
@ex<EM><EN>This hymn has been attributed to R’ Shlomo ibn Gabirol who lived in Spain during
the eleventh century. While praising God’s omnipotence and providence, it clarifies the
meaning of the name Adonoy so that before proceeding to pray, each worshiper
understands the significance of the God he is addressing.
