@ct<ENG>Yigdal
@ex<EM><EN>This hymn, written by Daniel ben Yehuda, who was a Dayan in Rome about 1300,
is based on Maimonides’ 13 principles of Judaism. According to Maimonides,
failure to believe in a single one of these principles places one outside the pale of
Judaism.
