@c1<ENG>Korban Tamid @12(Daily Offering)
@ex<EM><EN>The Tamid-offerings, two daily offerings of one lamb each, were offered once in
the morning and once in the afternoon. The former was the first public-offering
brought on the Altar each day. And the latter terminated the day’s offerings. These
animals were purchased from the annual half-shekel gifts of the people and were
offered on behalf of the entire Jewish People. Before reading this passage we offer
a brief prayer.
