@ex<EM><EN>This psalm (34) is based entirely on an event that took place in Dovid’s personal
life as related in 1 Shmuel 21:11±16. Forced to flee from Saul, he took refuge among
the Philistines, where he was recognized as the slayer of Goliath. In order to escape
death at the hands of his foes, Dovid pretended to be an imbecile, and was sent
away unharmed by King Avimelech.
