@ex<EM><EN>According to our Sages, Psalms 90 through 101, were said by Moshe. According
to Radak, Dovid actually found this psalm in its written form and knowing it to be
the prayer of Moshe, included it in his book of psalms. It speaks of the frailty of
man and the brevity of his life and asks for God’s compassion and favor despite his
wrongdoings.
