@ex<EM><EN>Rav S.R. Hirsch writes that the six concluding chapters of the Book of Psalms
are the most important gift of Dovid’s Divinely-inspired hymns. They are an
essential component of our daily prayers. Our Sages attach much significance to
Psalm 145 in particular, and stated: “Whoever recites ‘A praise by Dovid’ three
times a day is assuredly worthy of a share in the World to Come” (Berachos 4b).
When recited in prayer, this psalm is always introduced with two verses from other
Psalms (84:5 and 144:15). These verses contain the word fortunate three times, an
allusion to this psalm being recited three times a day. These verses are so closely
identified with Psalm 145 that it is commonly referred to as Ashrei (Fortunate).
