@ex<EM><EN>It has become a universally accepted custom to recite Barechu before proceeding
to the blessings of Shema. Barechu, like Kaddish and Kedushah, cannot be recited
unless a quorumĞa minyan of ten adult malesĞis present. Barechu is also said by
one who is called upon to read from the Torah.
@xe<EM><EN>The practice of saying Barechu is mentioned numerous times in the Talmud. It
is even cited in the Mishnah (Maseches Berachos 49b) in the names of Rabbi Akiva
and Rabbi Yishmael.
