@ct<ENG>Hymn of Glory
@ex<ALD-3><EM><EN>This closing hymn is called “Hymn of Glory” because it sings the praises and
great glory of God. According to some scholars, the hymn was composed by Rabbi
Samuel ben Kolonimus, the father of Rabbu Judah of Regensburg, known as Rabbi
Yehudah ha-Chassid, a saint and mystic. Others say that Rabbi Yehudah himself
wrote it.
